      • mutationTolerantIterator

        public Iterator<R> mutationTolerantIterator()
        Description copied from interface: Storage
        Returned iterator from this method doesn't throw ConcurrentModificationException to fail fast. Because fail fast may not be the desired behaviour always. For example if you are caching an iterator as in AbstractEvictableRecordStore.expirationIterator and you know that in next rounds you will eventually visit all entries, you don't need fail fast behaviour. Note that returned iterator is not thread-safe !!!
        Specified by:
        mutationTolerantIterator in interface Storage<Data,R extends Record>
        Returns:
        new iterator instance

      • getIfSameKey

        public R getIfSameKey(Data key)
        Description copied from interface: Storage
        Gives the same result as Storage.get(Object), but with the additional constraint that the supplied key must not just be equal to, but be exactly the same key blob (at the same memory address) as the one stored. The implementation of this method is only needed for the HD memory-based implementations.

      • fetchKeys

        public MapKeysWithCursor fetchKeys(int tableIndex,
                                   int size)
        Description copied from interface: Storage
        Fetch minimally size keys from the tableIndex position. The key is fetched on-heap.

        NOTE: The implementation is free to return more than size items. This can happen if we cannot easily resume from the last returned item by receiving the tableIndex of the last item. The index can represent a bucket with multiple items and in this case the returned object will contain all items in that bucket, regardless if we exceed the requested size.

        Specified by:
        fetchKeys in interface Storage<Data,R extends Record>
        Parameters:
        tableIndex - the index (position) from which to resume
        size - the minimal count of returned items
        Returns:
        fetched keys and the table index for keys AFTER the last returned key

      • fetchEntries

        public MapEntriesWithCursor fetchEntries(int tableIndex,
                                         int size,
                                         SerializationService serializationService)
        Description copied from interface: Storage
        Fetch minimally size items from the tableIndex position. Both the key and value are fetched on-heap.

        NOTE: The implementation is free to return more than size items. This can happen if we cannot easily resume from the last returned item by receiving the tableIndex of the last item. The index can represent a bucket with multiple items and in this case the returned object will contain all items in that bucket, regardless if we exceed the requested size.

        Specified by:
        fetchEntries in interface Storage<Data,R extends Record>
        Parameters:
        tableIndex - the index (position) from which to resume
        size - the minimal count of returned items
        Returns:
        fetched entries and the table index for entries AFTER the last returned entry
